<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="497" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,1816,2023]" lastBlockId="30.[151,1437,150,429]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="497" pageId="29" pageNumber="496">
Reports of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[280,519,1816,1842]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[280,519,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="496">Leptochiton belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[636,762,1816,1842]" name="Philippines" pageId="29" pageNumber="496">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(off Luzon Island and South of Mindanao Island (
<bibRefCitation author="Haddon, A. C." pageId="29" pageNumber="496" pagination="1 - 50" refId="ref10976" refString="Haddon, A. C. (1886) Report on the Polyplacophora collected by H. M. S. &quot; Challenger &quot; during the years 1873 - 76. Challenger Reports, 15, 1 - 50, pls. 1 - 3." type="journal article" year="1886">Haddon 1886</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P." box="[225,347,1852,1879]" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" pagination="175 - 186" refId="ref11101" refString="Kaas, P. (1990) New species and further records of known species of Polyplacophora from the tropical western Pacific. Basteria, 54, 175 - 186." type="journal article" year="1990">Kaas 1990</bibRefCitation>
) are erroneous. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko, B. &amp; Sellanes, J." box="[536,842,1852,1879]" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" pagination="259 - 279" refId="ref12331" refString="Sirenko, B. &amp; Sellanes, J. (2016) Update of the genus Leptochiton (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) in Chilean deep waters: three new reports and description of two new species. Zootaxa, 4173 (3), 259 - 279. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4173.3.5" type="journal article" year="2016">Sirenko &amp; Sellanes (2016)</bibRefCitation>
showed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[998,1126,1852,1878]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[998,1126,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="496">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1136,1278,1852,1879]" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" sensu="stricto">sensu stricto</taxonomicNameLabel>
occurs in the Pacific Ocean from Hokkaido (
<geoCoordinate box="[515,616,1888,1914]" degrees="40" direction="north" minutes="12" orientation="latitude" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" precision="925" value="40.2">40°12’N</geoCoordinate>
), via the Sea of Okhotsk into the Bering Sea, and in North and South America’s Pacific waters southwards to 
<geoCoordinate box="[604,698,1924,1950]" degrees="42" direction="south" minutes="40" orientation="latitude" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" precision="925" value="-42.666668">42°40’S</geoCoordinate>
, at depths of 
<quantity box="[850,1018,1924,1951]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9119999999999997" metricValueMax="3.7239999999999993" metricValueMin="0.1" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" unit="m" value="1912.0" valueMax="3724.0" valueMin="100.0">100 to 3724 m</quantity>
. The closest deep-sea relatives of the Philippine specimens that were assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[645,771,1960,1986]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[645,771,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="496">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nierstrasz, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[821,1148,1960,1987]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[821,938,1960,1986]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="496">L. simplex</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nierstrasz, H. F." box="[953,1140,1960,1987]" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref11484" refString="Nierstrasz, H. F. (1905) Die Chitonen der Siboga-Expedition. Siboga Expeditie, 48, 1 - 112, pls. 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1905">Nierstrasz, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Makassar Strait and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nierstrasz, 1905)" baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[198,545,1996,2023]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[198,337,1997,2022]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="496">L. giganteus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Nierstrasz, H. F." box="[351,537,1996,2023]" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" pagination="1 - 112" refId="ref11484" refString="Nierstrasz, H. F. (1905) Die Chitonen der Siboga-Expedition. Siboga Expeditie, 48, 1 - 112, pls. 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1905">Nierstrasz, 1905</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from the Banda Sea. These two species were synonymized as either 
<taxonomicName authority="(M. Sars MS, Loven, 1846)" baseAuthorityName="M. Sars MS, Loven" baseAuthorityYear="1846" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="497" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="29" pageNumber="496" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alveolus">
<emphasis box="[1314,1436,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="496">L. alveolus</emphasis>
(M. Sars MS, 
<bibRefCitation author="Loven, S. L." box="[312,455,151,178]" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" pagination="134 - 160" refId="ref11366" refString="Loven, S. L. (1846) Index molluscorum litora Scandinaviae Occidentalia habitantium. Ofverssigt Af Kungel Svenska Vetenskaps- Akademiens Forhandlinger, 3, 134 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59081" type="journal article" year="1846">Lovén, 1846</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, A. J." box="[536,692,151,177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" pagination="145 - 165" refId="ref10783" refString="Ferreira, A. J. (1979) The family Lepidopleuridae (Mollusca: Polyplacophora) in the eastern Pacific. The Veliger, 22, 145 - 165." type="journal article" year="1979">Ferreira 1979</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P &amp; Van Belle, R. A." box="[704,973,150,177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" refId="ref11172" refString="Kaas, P &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985) Monograph of living chitons. 1. Order Neoloricata: Lepidopleurina. E. J. Brill / W., Backhuys, Leiden, 240 pp." type="book" year="1985">Kaas &amp; Van Belle 1985</bibRefCitation>
) and or as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[1100,1227,151,177]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[1100,1227,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A." pageId="30" pageNumber="497" refId="ref11214" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1987) Monograph of living chitons. Vol. 3. Suborder Ischnochitonina: Ischnochitonidae: Chaetopleurinae, and Ischnochitoninae. E. J. Brill / W, Backhuys, Leiden, 302 pp." type="book" year="1987">Kaas &amp; Van Belle 1987</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko, B. I." box="[295,464,186,213]" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" pagination="151 - 202" refId="ref12057" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2015) Shallow and deep-sea chitons of the genus Leptochiton Gray, 1847 (Mollusca: Polyplacophora: Lepidopleurida) from Peruvian and Chilean waters. Zootaxa, 4033 (2), 151 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4033.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sirenko (2015)</bibRefCitation>
already discussed that the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[762,887,187,213]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[762,887,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group comprises several taxa that should be considered valid including 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[412,549,223,248]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis box="[412,549,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L. giganteus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[742,867,223,249]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[742,867,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the width of the jugal sinus almost equal to the width of the apophyses (whereas the width of the jugal sinus is much wider than the apophyses in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[1302,1426,259,285]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[1302,1426,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by having dorsal scales without ribs. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[621,849,295,321]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="simplex">
<emphasis box="[621,849,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">Leptochiton simplex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was treated as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Thiele, 1909)" baseAuthorityName="Thiele" baseAuthorityYear="1909" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis box="[1186,1436,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">Leptochiton japonicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele, J." box="[159,304,331,357]" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref12559" refString="Thiele, J. (1909 - 1910) Revision des Systems der Chitonen. Teil. 1. Zoologica, 22, 1 - 70, figs. A-E, pls. 1 - 6 (1909); 71 - 132, pls. 7 - 10 (1910)." type="journal article" year="1909">Thiele, 1909</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko, B. I." box="[355,524,330,357]" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" pagination="151 - 202" refId="ref12057" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2015) Shallow and deep-sea chitons of the genus Leptochiton Gray, 1847 (Mollusca: Polyplacophora: Lepidopleurida) from Peruvian and Chilean waters. Zootaxa, 4033 (2), 151 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4033.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sirenko (2015)</bibRefCitation>
but is here re-instated as valid species, which differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[1190,1317,331,357]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[1190,1317,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having dorsal scales with 6 ribs (vs. 2–3 ribs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[594,719,367,393]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[594,719,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). I suggest to preliminarily call specimens that have been identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[232,358,403,429]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[232,358,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the above-mentioned works 
<emphasis box="[712,735,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">L.</emphasis>
? 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[754,850,403,429]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="30" pageNumber="497" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[754,850,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="497">belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until these specimens can be studied in more detail.
</paragraph>
